      "@id": "https://ssbd.riken.jp/v3/project/451-Hitora-Neopetromin",
      "@type": "Dataset",
      "identifier": "451-Hitora-Neopetromin",
      "name": "The shape of vacuole and F-actin in tobacco BY-2 cells treated with neopetromin, a newly found peptide",
      "description": "HPLC-MS analysis revealed the presence of an\nunreported peptide in the extract of the marine sponge Neopetrosia\nsp. Its structure was determined as a tripeptide, named\nneopetromin (1), composed of two tyrosine and one tryptophan\nresidues with a heteroaromatic C−N cross-link between side\nchains. The absolute configuration of amino acids was determined\nusing Marfey’s method after ozonolysis and hydrolysis of 1.\nCompound 1 promoted vacuole fragmentation in an actin-\nindependent manner in tobacco BY-2 cells.",
      "datePublished": "2025-11-28",
      "license": "https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/",
      "keywords": [
        "Microscopy, Confocal",
